Now...

12:32.695 --> 12:34.095
who am I speaking to?

12:34.163 --> 12:35.363
No real names.

12:35.431 --> 12:36.598
Say Shabazzleford.

12:36.665 --> 12:38.667
Sha... Dave.

12:38.734 --> 12:40.435
Mmm...

12:40.503 --> 12:43.305
Will Gloria be joining us?

12:44.507 --> 12:46.375
I am Gloria.

12:48.611 --> 12:50.879
So, Dave...

12:52.716 --> 12:54.717
...who should we thank
for this referral?

12:54.784 --> 12:57.019
(sniffing)

12:57.087 --> 12:58.187
It's not her, Dave.

12:59.323 --> 13:00.556
(sighs)

13:00.624 --> 13:02.058
I'm sorry.

13:02.125 --> 13:04.961
I-I think I've
made a mistake.

13:05.028 --> 13:06.128
I-I should really leave.

13:06.196 --> 13:07.329
Who told you about us, Dave?

13:09.032 --> 13:10.499
Oh, there's no need
to be nervous.

13:12.869 --> 13:14.904
Michael.

13:14.972 --> 13:17.307
Michael McDerry.

13:17.375 --> 13:19.042
Oh...

13:19.109 --> 13:21.144
Well, why didn't you say so?

13:21.211 --> 13:23.980
Michael's a really good
friend of the agency's.

13:24.048 --> 13:25.081
Come on.
(clicks tongue)

13:25.149 --> 13:26.249
Follow.

13:28.286 --> 13:30.487
♪ ♪

13:32.357 --> 13:33.724
Whoa.

13:33.792 --> 13:35.726
You know what this place is.

13:35.794 --> 13:38.428
The nether regions have got
to be here somewhere.

13:38.496 --> 13:39.863
I'll find them.

13:39.931 --> 13:41.931
(chimes)

13:45.736 --> 13:47.603
By the way, Dave,

13:47.671 --> 13:50.539
I feel like I need
to be candid with you:

13:50.607 --> 13:53.776
We absolutely forbid
the involvement of children.

13:53.843 --> 13:56.011
But I am more than happy

13:56.079 --> 13:57.513
to watch over the baby

13:57.581 --> 13:58.981
while you and your dog

13:59.049 --> 14:00.850
realize your very own
unique, special fantasy.

14:00.851 --> 14:02.351
No...
So you just let me know

14:02.419 --> 14:04.153
when you see something
you like, okay?

14:04.221 --> 14:06.389
(chuckles)

14:09.894 --> 14:11.028
She's here.

14:11.095 --> 14:12.662
Are you sure?
Positive.

14:12.730 --> 14:14.064
Are you chewing gum?

14:14.131 --> 14:16.633
No. Dogs can't
chew gum, Ryan.

14:16.701 --> 14:17.668
(phone ringing)

14:17.735 --> 14:18.969
Shit.

14:19.037 --> 14:21.305
Kristen. How's dinner?

14:21.372 --> 14:22.673
KRISTEN:
Ryan, where the hell are you?

14:22.741 --> 14:25.043
Where is Joffrey?
Is Joffrey okay?

14:25.110 --> 14:27.412
R-Ryan?

14:27.479 --> 14:28.980
Ryan!

14:30.916 --> 14:32.617
Oh... Hey, guys.

14:32.685 --> 14:35.386
Uh, sorry to scare
you like that.

14:35.454 --> 14:37.989
How come you're back so early?

14:38.057 --> 14:39.891
Someone broke
into Michael's car.

14:39.959 --> 14:41.659
Oh...

14:41.727 --> 14:42.994
Oh, God.

14:43.062 --> 14:44.563
You took Joffrey out
without his hat?

14:44.630 --> 14:45.864
He could've gotten pneumonia.

14:45.932 --> 14:47.332
I'm sorry.
I didn't think about it..

14:47.400 --> 14:48.633
I actually did think about it,

14:48.701 --> 14:50.135
but I wanted Joffrey
to catch pneumonia,

14:50.202 --> 14:51.903
'cause, well...
dude's a dick.

14:51.970 --> 14:53.210
That was so
irresponsible, Ryan.

14:53.239 --> 14:54.573
It is pretty cold out there.

14:54.640 --> 14:56.141
Really?

14:56.209 --> 14:57.476
You're the last person

14:57.543 --> 14:59.311
that should be passing
judgment on anyone.

14:59.379 --> 15:00.479
Excuse me?
I know what you've been doing

15:00.547 --> 15:01.647
at Gloria's.

15:01.715 --> 15:03.582
What?
Who's Gloria?

15:03.650 --> 15:06.018
Yeah, Michael, who is Gloria?

15:06.085 --> 15:08.554
She's just, um...
You know what?

15:08.622 --> 15:10.656
I'd rather not talk about her.
Oh, because you don't want

15:10.724 --> 15:12.125
to tell Kristen
about the illegal brothel

15:12.192 --> 15:13.693
that you've been frequenting?

15:13.761 --> 15:15.762
I'm sorry to be the one
to tell you this,

15:15.830 --> 15:17.830
but Michael
was with a prostitute

15:17.898 --> 15:19.866
right before he picked you up
for your date tonight.

15:19.934 --> 15:21.267
Ryan, what the hell
are you talking about?

15:21.335 --> 15:22.635
Are you insane?

15:22.703 --> 15:23.570
MICHAEL:
No, it's...

15:23.638 --> 15:25.171
it's true.

15:26.440 --> 15:28.074
But-but it's not what you think.

15:28.142 --> 15:30.243
The prostitute was a patient.

15:30.311 --> 15:31.845
Patient?

15:31.912 --> 15:33.880
Michael's a gynecologist, Ryan.

15:33.948 --> 15:35.382
Yeah, I do pro bono work

15:35.449 --> 15:36.783
for an organization
called Safety First.

15:36.851 --> 15:38.118
Most of the women are illegals.

15:38.186 --> 15:39.620
They're scared, uneducated,

15:39.687 --> 15:41.288
and they don't have access
to health insurance.

15:41.356 --> 15:44.359
So I perform free
blood work, Pap smears.

15:44.426 --> 15:46.628
In fact, earlier tonight,

15:46.695 --> 15:48.129
I had to make
an emergency visit

15:48.197 --> 15:49.677
because one of the women
was suffering

15:49.699 --> 15:51.260
from an infection
of the nether regions.

15:51.267 --> 15:53.569
You know, I have to say,
the fact that

15:53.637 --> 15:55.838
you snooped around
and secretly gathered

15:55.905 --> 15:57.185
all of this information
about me,

15:57.206 --> 15:58.840
it makes me very uncomfortable.

15:58.908 --> 16:00.108
Michael, I hope you
know I had nothing...

16:00.176 --> 16:01.257
I-I think I'd better leave.

16:04.713 --> 16:07.214
Well, Ryan, you were right.

16:07.282 --> 16:08.916
I guess I was letting
a crazy person

16:08.983 --> 16:10.818
hang around Joffrey: you.

16:10.885 --> 16:11.919
No...
You can obviously forget

16:11.986 --> 16:13.520
about the legal guardianship.

16:13.587 --> 16:15.255
Kristen, wait.

16:15.322 --> 16:16.623
Oh, my God.

16:16.690 --> 16:20.293
Are those... ants?

16:20.361 --> 16:23.396
Not just any ants.

16:23.464 --> 16:24.698
KRISTEN: Ugh!
(door closes)

16:30.659 --> 16:33.199
Oh, you love Joffrey now?
Look at his hairline!

16:33.319 --> 16:35.086
It's only gonna get worse.

16:35.154 --> 16:36.888
You tattooed his name

16:36.955 --> 16:38.689
on the inside of
your lower lip?!

16:38.757 --> 16:40.758
Gah!

16:40.826 --> 16:43.828
If I can't have
you, no one will!

16:43.895 --> 16:45.096
(grunts)

16:45.163 --> 16:46.564
Just let it happen.

16:46.632 --> 16:48.432
Into the light.

16:48.500 --> 16:50.367
Shh...

16:52.104 --> 16:53.271
Oh, hey, Ryan. What's up?

16:53.338 --> 16:54.572
"What's up?"

16:54.640 --> 16:56.040
Thanks to your little
love triangle,

16:56.107 --> 16:57.375
my sister isn't speaking to me.

16:57.442 --> 16:59.611
Hey, I'm a victim here, too.

16:59.678 --> 17:01.919
If Bear hadn't messed around
with one of my best friends,

17:01.947 --> 17:02.914
none of this would've happened.

17:02.982 --> 17:05.150
Nobody messed around
with anybody.

17:05.217 --> 17:07.484
Bear is a stuffed animal,
and Joffrey is a baby.

17:07.553 --> 17:10.589
The relationship between Bear
and Joffrey is very real.

17:10.656 --> 17:12.424
And he's not a baby
where it counts!

17:12.492 --> 17:14.894
Okay. You want
to play this game?

17:14.962 --> 17:17.096
You say you want Bear
to meet someone else,

17:17.164 --> 17:18.631
but the second Bear
actually does,

17:18.699 --> 17:20.200
you freak out

17:20.267 --> 17:22.269
and start interfering
and sabotaging.

17:22.336 --> 17:24.369
You talking about me and Bear
or you and Kristen?

17:24.438 --> 17:26.306
What?

17:28.042 --> 17:29.777
(chuckling):
Ryan...

17:29.844 --> 17:31.645
we're a crazy pair.

17:31.713 --> 17:34.014
Sometimes, when you think
you're looking out for...

17:34.082 --> 17:35.249
Jesus!

17:35.317 --> 17:38.352
Why won't you...

17:38.420 --> 17:41.588
die?!

17:45.193 --> 17:46.493
Ryan, aren't you
going to introduce me

17:46.561 --> 17:47.494
to your new friend?

17:47.562 --> 17:49.029
This bear is for Joffrey.

17:49.097 --> 17:50.831
(laughs)

17:50.899 --> 17:52.666
What's up,
Responsible Insurance?

17:52.734 --> 17:54.468
(laughing)
Huh?

17:54.536 --> 17:56.337
Oh, you know, from earlier.

17:56.404 --> 17:58.873
The insurance company we went
to, and then in the back room

17:58.940 --> 18:00.608
they were running
the prostitution ring?

18:00.675 --> 18:02.843
And since you're offering
the new bear to Joffrey,

18:02.911 --> 18:06.113
you're sort of running
your own quasi-prostitution...

18:06.181 --> 18:07.314
Whatever.
You don't get it.

18:07.382 --> 18:09.117
No, I get it.

18:11.320 --> 18:12.954
What are you doing here?

18:13.022 --> 18:15.323
(high-pitched voice):
Hi, Kristen.

18:15.391 --> 18:18.426
Your brother Ryan sent me over
to say he's sorry.

18:19.796 --> 18:21.463
Can we talk?

18:21.531 --> 18:23.451
Only if you promise
never to do that voice again.

18:25.101 --> 18:26.935
Maybe on some level,

18:27.003 --> 18:29.405
I'm worried that if you find
happiness with someone,

18:29.472 --> 18:31.073
you won't need me anymore.

18:31.141 --> 18:32.775
Ryan, you're my brother.

18:32.843 --> 18:35.111
I'll always need you.
And so will Joffrey.

18:35.179 --> 18:36.659
You know, in case
you haven't noticed,

18:36.714 --> 18:38.915
you're not the only one
who needs to feel needed.

18:38.983 --> 18:41.184
I guess we both have some issues
we have to work out.

18:43.688 --> 18:46.757
And then I said, "What's up,
Responsible Insurance?"

18:46.825 --> 18:48.860
(chuckles)
Exactly!

18:48.927 --> 18:50.561
Thank you!

18:50.629 --> 18:52.549
Would it help if I called
Michael and apologized?

18:52.563 --> 18:54.931
Nah, don't bother. I doubt it
would've worked out anyway.

18:54.999 --> 18:57.100
He drives a Honda.
And he's so pale.

18:57.167 --> 18:59.602
Anyway, that's the last time
I let Dad set me up.

18:59.669 --> 19:01.103
Dad?

19:01.171 --> 19:02.504
You said you met him at yoga.

19:02.572 --> 19:04.640
Well, yeah, well, I lied.

19:04.707 --> 19:06.908
I figured you'd freak out
if you knew Dad was involved.

19:06.976 --> 19:08.376
But here is the truth, Ryan:

19:08.444 --> 19:10.178
Dad met a wonderful guy,

19:10.246 --> 19:12.380
and he thought he'd be perfect
for his daughter.

19:12.448 --> 19:14.516
And I know you think Dad's
always up to something,

19:14.584 --> 19:16.718
but it's not true.
He isn't out to get you.

19:16.786 --> 19:17.953
In fact, he was the one

19:18.020 --> 19:19.381
who convinced me
to let you babysit

19:19.389 --> 19:21.189
when he had to cancel
at the last minute.

19:21.257 --> 19:23.625
Dad was the original
babysitter?

19:23.693 --> 19:24.993
Yeah. Why?

