MAN:
Well, this is a surprise.

19:38.342 --> 19:39.843
Let me be clear:

19:39.910 --> 19:42.011
I'm not calling to say hello
or to catch up.

19:42.079 --> 19:43.647
I just have one thing to say.

19:43.714 --> 19:45.382
All right, well...

19:45.450 --> 19:47.490
This is a strange way
to open our first conversation

19:47.552 --> 19:49.686
in over a year, Ryan,
but go ahead.

19:49.754 --> 19:50.954
I know what you did.

19:51.022 --> 19:52.189
Okay.

19:52.256 --> 19:53.456
What did I do?

19:53.524 --> 19:55.492
Setting Kristen up with Michael,

19:55.560 --> 19:57.193
offering to babysit,

19:57.261 --> 19:58.962
canceling at the last minute

19:59.030 --> 20:00.898
and advising her to call me.

20:00.965 --> 20:03.400
You knew I'd screw things up
with Kristen.

20:03.467 --> 20:05.469
You wanted me to,

20:05.537 --> 20:08.038
so that she'd give you the legal
guardianship, and not me.

20:09.207 --> 20:11.308
It was a giant manipulation.

20:13.311 --> 20:16.814
Do you realize
how crazy that sounds?

20:16.882 --> 20:20.318
I'm not the bad guy, Ryan.

20:20.386 --> 20:23.087
Just stay out of my life.

20:23.155 --> 20:24.422
Ryan, wait.

20:27.259 --> 20:29.928
It was good
to hear your voice, son.

